Dominican Alfredo Ricart will take overas executive director of the International Sugar Organization(ISO) in mid-April, ISO officer in charge Constantin Politoffsaid.    Previous ISO chief William Miller retired at end-Februarylast year.    Ricart told Reuters his first aim is put the "house in order"by having a new administrative sugar pact with improvedallocations of voting rights and financial contributions.    Once this is done, time can be dedicated to working towardsa new International Sugar Agreement (ISA) with economicclauses, he said.    Ricart, currently the Dominican Republic's ambassador toAustria, the Netherlands and the UN in Geneva, said he willvisit the four major exporters - Australia, Brazil, Cuba andthe European Community - to talk to governments and producersand find out about problems that are preventing these countriesfinding common ground for a new sugar pact. Reuter&#3;